summary: The document is a classified communication concerning the release of information under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992. It details the receipt of an incomplete fax, which includes a cover sheet, a one-page cable from Copenhagen marked 'NO TRACES', and the first page of a director cable requesting traces on 'LEE HARVEY OSWALD'. The document underscores the importance of deleting crypts prior to release and asks to be notified of the release date to inform relevant parties.
key_findings: The document pertains to the release of classified information under the JFK Assassination Records Act.
It references a request for traces on Lee Harvey Oswald, linking it to the JFK assassination investigation.
Procedural issues are highlighted, including the incompleteness of received materials and the need for crypt deletion before release.
There is a specific request to inform certain parties about the release date of the documents.
